OL,7,FThree in five (61%) of those polled in
OL,8,F2024 said they may not raise concerns
OL,9,Fbecause they were "afraid" they they
OL,10,For colleagues could be "unfairly
OL,11,Fblamed or suffer adverse consequences".
OL,13,FMeanwhile 45% said they feel that
OL,14,Ftheir managers discourage them from
OL,15,Fraising concerns ` up from 20% in 2018.
OL,17,FThe BMA said that doctors are now
OL,18,F"more frightened than ever" to speak
OL,19,Fup when they see patient safety
OL,20,Fissues, or levels of care at risk.
